<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Splaktar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">So far I've been looking to buy my spells now that I'm 56...  the 58-60 spells haven't been so hard to find (just been doing Jugs raids).  But I cannot for the life of me seem to find my 55-57 spells.  Camped fungi king for ages, did a ton of breaks for Trak, jugs raids, etc.<P>Mark of Karn - been offering 10k and no one has the spell or is interested<BR>Word of Restoration - talked to a guy last night who wanted 5k+ for this<BR>Aegis - people seem to rarely have this, but will let it go for around 2k<BR>Fortitude - it sucks, but no one has it and no one sells it... I've been offering 1-2k..<P>55-60 Kunark spells seem to generally sell for 1-15k (most in the 2-5k range) on Fennin Ro.  But cleric spells seem to be the most rare of them all...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">MoK and Aegis are just extremely rare, so you won't find too many if any copies on the market.<P>The others seem to come most often from druids and necros soloing in skyfire. I got Word of Restoration for 1k and Fortitude for 500pp.<P>Cleric spells only seem to be rarest because it's you looking for them =) Seriously though, except for WoR and Naltron's Mark the dropped Kunark spells you can do without and not miss them. It's a much better situation that say, magicians, who have to pay 15k for the spell that makes a big difference in what they can lend to a group or raid.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Irysangel</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Exactly how rare is Naltron's Mark? We did Juggs the other day and it dropped twice in one hour, but other than that I've never seen it drop on any other Jugg raid we've done.<P>Is it extremely rare? Was wondering if a guild would be able to get purchaseable copies for the clerics in their guild or is this just a silly idea?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jubal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think Naltron's Mark is fairly rare as well, though not on the order of MoK or Aegis. I was without until a guild necro (level 51 heh) got a copy while soloing in skyfire... I know of other clerics 58+ from fairly powerful guilds who have not been able to find this spell, so I consider myself damned lucky.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corynthia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Me got Mark of karn and Word of restoration in skyfire, when me group were killing named drakes.  we got also several other spells.<BR>great zone for spell drops.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR>so for I have been very lucky in spells, only bought one(heroic bond) but got rather pissed when me got it in FV at the spell trader  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><BR>oh well<P>------------------<BR>Corynthia-Dominion of Unity<BR>53rd Level Dwarven Vicar<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Splaktar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hrm, I wouldn't say 'they only seem rare because I'm looking for them'  because I also have a lvl 53 necro and his spells were not this hard to find (even the 56 pet).<P>As for Naltron's Mark, in 3 Jugs raids of 5-7 hours each, this has only dropped once.  I was lucky enough to get it.  In that time we've had pretty bad cleric drops overall, 3 enforced reverence, 1 divine intervention, 1 naltron's mark, 5 trepidation (buyable).  In that same time we've seen almost every other spell for every other class (other than shaman malo/avatar).<P>------------------<BR>Splaktar/Gurgel/Samas</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Skrimgeour Kuchenhyrst</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Irys,<P>I offered a cleric 15K for it and was turned down.<P>Skrim</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Splaktar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Finally picked up MoK for 5k this week.  Got it from a druid who was soloing in BW.  He had it on a mule in RV, boggle.<P>Managed to get Aegis from another cleric who had a spare copy.<P>Still no luck on Fortitude or Word of Restoration.<P>Offered a cleric who had MoK 10k for it the other day and she said no, heh.<P>------------------<BR>Splaktar/Gurgel/Samas</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Beckett</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yay, I finally got Mark of Karn tonight!  A few weeks ago a friend of a friend mentioned that so-and-so might have MoK for sale.  So for ten days straight I bugged the guy with tells, trying to outbid any other offers he was getting.  Tonight he traded it to me for an Ornate Runed Blade and a Blue Diamond.<p>[This message has been edited by Beckett (edited 05-25-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kegen D'Eire</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> you know i dunno if its just me,but having<BR>to buy spells at those prices from other<BR>players is about the stupidest crap ive<BR>ever heard.<P>  if i got ANY 50+ spell that another class<BR>can use,ill GIVE them the damn spell for<BR>free,because you never know,it might actually<BR>help me out someday.<P>   it just boggles my mind how friggin<BR>greedy people in this game are /shrug<P>Kegen D'Eire<Honored Circle><BR>54 Dark Elf Vicar<BR>Xev</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Zygote</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR>when kunark first came out, plenty of greedy bastards tried to rape people on spell prices. a year later, most people give away the 51-54 spells.<P>herioc bond was at one time like 5k, now its like 500pp.<P>i've gotten naltrons mark and word of restoration in  skyfire. never did get mok though. <P>generally speaking most people give spells to guildmates and theres really no need to sell them on the market</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Avenea</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I payed:<P>10k for Naltrons Mark<BR>1 BD bracer for Aegolism (back when they were worth 10k)<BR>8k for MoK<P>The rest I just looted.<P><P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.elementofdarkness.com/eqi/inv.asp?char=189" TARGET=_blank>Avenea Arach'Daemos - High Priestess</A><BR>Cazic-Thule<BR> <A HREF="http://www.elementofdarkness.com" TARGET=_blank>www.elementofdarkness.com</A> </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
